Considered one of India’s top-ranked universities for postgraduate and research studies, Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU) is a public central university that has been given the status of ‘University of Excellence' by the UGC. It has been accredited by the NAAC with a Grade Point of 3.91 (on a scale of 4) and has been ranked 2 in the 'University' category by the NIRF 2022 Rankings. When it comes to the international position, JNU has been ranked among the top 10 Indian Universities under QS World University rankings. The University has also become India’s first-ever University to offer foreign language courses within its Integrated MA programme. Presently, JNU comprises 13 schools, 55 centres and seven special centres. The varsity offers over 106 courses across several streams at UG, PG and PhD levels. In addition, it also offers Certificate, Diploma and Advanced Diploma courses in various languages. Formerly known as Delhi College of Engineering, Delhi Technological University (DTU) was established in 1941. The university is accredited by the NAAC with an 'A' grade and is also approved by the University Grant Commission (UGC). DTU ranked 35 for ‘Engineering’, 38 for ‘University’ and 63 for ‘Overall’ category by the NIRF Rankings 2022. DTU is counted amongst the oldest Engineering colleges in India. DTU currently offers more than 80 courses via its 17 departments. Out of these departments, the University School of Management and Entrepreneurship (USME) was established recently and is also known as the DTU East Delhi Campus. Additionally, DTU formed the Delhi School of Management (DSM) as a department under it to offer courses in the field of Management. All the UG, PG and doctoral programmes available in the field of Engineering, Design, Science and Management, among others, are offered together via DTU’s main campus, DSM and the University School of Management & Entrepreneurship (USME). The NorthCap University was established in 1996 by Educate India Society. The NorthCap University has been given a rank band of 151-200 by NIRF 2023 among the best Universities in India. The National Assessment and Accreditation Council (NAAC) has awarded NCU Grade A accreditation. The University Grants Commission (UGC) and the Bar Council of India (BCI) both recognise NCU. The NorthCap University has achieved an overall rating of DIAMOND from QS I-Gauge. The university has four schools offering courses at the undergraduate, graduate and doctoral levels, namely the School of Engineering & Technology, School of Management and Liberal Studies, School of Law, as well as a Department of Applied Sciences and Centre for Languages Learning.
